Fishing Forecast is the ultimate tool for anglers of all skill levels. Whether you're a seasoned pro or just starting out, this app will help you make the most of your fishing trips. By using the most accurate atmospheric pressure data, Fishing Forecast can predict the best times for you to cast your line and increase your chances of a successful catch.

With Fishing Forecast, you can easily keep track of the current weather conditions in your area, as well as the upcoming forecast. The app uses real-time data to provide you with the most up-to-date information, so you can plan your fishing trip accordingly. Additionally, Fishing Forecast displays information on wave height and swell period where possible, giving you a comprehensive overview of the conditions on the water.

One of the best things about Fishing Forecast is that it works anywhere in the world. Whether you're fishing in a local pond or on a remote river in another country, you can rely on this app to provide you with accurate information about the best times to fish.

App Features:

- Fish biting forecast based on weather changes;
- Atmospheric pressure and its fluctuations;
- Air and water temperature;
- Wind direction and speed;
- Moon phases and their influence on fish biting;
- Sunrise, sunset, and moonrise times;
- Precipitation probability and amount;
- Air humidity;
- Cloud cover and its density;
- Visibility on the water;
- Ultraviolet (UV) index;
- Wave height and period (where available);
- Graphical display of weather data with historical trends.

The "Fishing Forecast" app is versatile and suitable for catching a wide variety of fish species. It’s helpful for those targeting predatory fish like pike, perch, and zander, as well as for anglers going after peaceful species such as carp, crucian carp, bream, roach, and more. No matter what type of fish you're after, the app will help you find the best time for a successful catch.

Fishing Forecast is available on iOS in free version. Download Fishing Forecast today and start catching more fish on your next trip!
